{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2109a","heading":"State and private forest landscape-scale restoration program","label":"2109a State and private forest landscape-scale restoration program","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch41","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Codificationand enacted identical sections. was repealed by .Pub. L. 110–234Pub. L. 110–246Pub. L. 110–234section 4(a) of Pub. L. 110–246","Amendments2018— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to competitive allocation of funds to State foresters or equivalent State officials.Pub. L. 115–334","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateEnactment of this section and repeal of by effective , the date of enactment of , see , set out as a note under , Agriculture.Pub. L. 110–234Pub. L. 110–246Pub. L. 110–234section 4 of Pub. L. 110–246section 8701 of Title 7May 22, 2008"],"amendments":["Amendments2018— amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to competitive allocation of funds to State foresters or equivalent State officials.Pub. L. 115–334"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Purpose","label":"a Purpose","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The purpose of this section is to encourage collaborative, science-based restoration of priority forest landscapes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Definitions","label":"b Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Indian tribe","label":"1 Indian tribe","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Indian tribe” has the meaning given the term in .section 5304 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Nonindustrial private forest land","label":"2 Nonindustrial private forest land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is rural, as determined by the Secretary;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has existing tree cover or is suitable for growing trees; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is owned by any private individual, group, association, corporation, Indian tribe, or other private legal entity.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"State forest land","label":"3 State forest land","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is rural, as determined by the Secretary; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/b/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fb%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is under State or local governmental ownership and considered to be non-Federal forest land.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Establishment","label":"c Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary, in consultation with State foresters or appropriate State agencies, shall establish a competitive grant program to provide financial and technical assistance to encourage collaborative, science-based restoration of priority forest landscapes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Eligibility","label":"d Eligibility","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is complete or substantially complete;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is for a multiyear period;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"covers nonindustrial private forest land or State forest land;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is accessible by wood-processing infrastructure; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fd%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is based on the best available science.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Plan criteria","label":"e Plan criteria","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to reduce the risk of uncharacteristic wildfires;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to improve fish and wildlife habitats, including the habitats of threatened and endangered species;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to maintain or improve water quality and watershed function;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to mitigate invasive species, insect infestation, and disease;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to improve important forest ecosystems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to measure ecological and economic benefits, including air quality and soil quality and productivity; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fe%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to take other relevant actions, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Priorities","label":"f Priorities","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"further a statewide forest assessment and resource strategy;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"promote cross boundary landscape collaboration; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"leverage public and private resources.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Collaboration and consultation","label":"g Collaboration and consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"administration of the program established under this section; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identification of other applicable resources for landscape-scale restoration.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":"Matching funds required","label":"h Matching funds required","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"As a condition of receiving a grant under this section, the Secretary shall require the recipient of the grant to provide funds or in-kind support from non-Federal sources in an amount that is at least equal to the amount of Federal funds.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":"Coordination and proximity encouraged","label":"i Coordination and proximity encouraged","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Collaborative Forest Landscape Restoration Program established under ;section 7303 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"landscape areas designated for insect and disease treatments under ;section 6591a of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"good neighbor authority under section 2113 of this title;1So in original. See .1section 2113a of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"stewardship end result contracting projects authorized under ;section 6591c of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"appropriate State-level programs; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fi%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"other relevant programs, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"j","heading":"Regulations","label":"j Regulations","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fj","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall promulgate such regulations as the Secretary determines necessary to carry out this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"k","heading":"Report","label":"k Report","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fk","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fk%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the status of development, execution, and administration of selected projects;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fk%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the accounting of program funding expenditures; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fk%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"specific accomplishments that have resulted from landscape-scale projects.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"l","heading":"Fund","label":"l Fund","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fl","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fl%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is established in the Treasury a fund, to be known as the “State and Private Forest Landscape-Scale Restoration Fund” (referred to in this subsection as the “Fund”), to be used by the Secretary to make grants under this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Contents","label":"2 Contents","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fl%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Fund shall consist of such amounts as are appropriated to the Fund under paragraph (3).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"3 Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s2109a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs2109a%2Fl%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to the Fund $20,000,000 for each fiscal year beginning with the first full fiscal year after , through fiscal year 2023, to remain available until expended.December 20, 2018","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
